**$effect**

In Svelte, `$effect` is used to create effects that run after the component has been mounted to the DOM and in a microtask after state changes. Effects can be batched and happen after any DOM updates have been applied.

```javascript
// Example of using $effect
$effect(() => {
  // Code to run as an effect
});
```

**Teardown Functions**

Effects can return teardown functions that will run immediately before the effect re-runs or when the component is destroyed. Teardown functions are used to clean up resources, such as clearing intervals.

